article.headline: Denver 75, Ark.-Pine Bluff 56
article.story: DENVER -- Brian Stafford had a game-high 19 points and Andrew Hooper added 18 to lead Denver to a 75-56 victory over Arkansas-Pine Bluff Sunday. Stafford sunk 5 of 6 from behind the 3-point line. Hooper came off the bench and made 7 of 13 from the field. Nate Rohnert added 16 points and nine assists for the Pioneers (1-1). Lebaron Weathers led the Lions (0-2) with 18 points, and Savalance Townsend added 10. The Lions started out strong, building a 7-0 lead before allowing Denver to catch up. The teams traded the lead late in the first half until the Pioneers carried a slim 40-36 lead into halftime. But Denver came off the break with an 8-0 scoring run and kept padding the lead.
